@Deleted User it was great! maybe cooked the tofu a bit too much because some of the smaller pieces were pretty crispy, which isn’t what u really want for scrambled tofu. i just made some whole wheat pasta and added salt to the boiling water like halfway in, and heated the tofu in olive oil for a bit then crushed it into smaller pieces; that’s basically the jist of t
it*
if i recall correctly, i combined the ingredients and seasoned them w/ salt, pepper, onion powder, garlic powder and cumin
if you’ve never had much success with tofu id recommend trying a tofu press
which is great for getting the moisture out

Chili: 1. In the bottom of stove pot, sauté chopped red pearl onions with chopped green peppers and cayenne pepper powder in light olive oil and (optional white wine) until onions are browned. 2. Add 1 can diced tomatoes, 1 can diced tomatoes w/ green chili peppers, 1 can diced tomatoes (chili ready), 1 can Annie's Vegan Medium Chili, stir. 3. Stir ingredients together and let simmer on medium-low heat. 4. Add 1 can of dark red kidney beans (no sodium), 1 can of black beans, and 1 can of Mild or Medium light red kidney beans. 5. Let simmer on medium heat, stirring often. 6. Add 4 pouches or cans of chunk light tuna, stir into pot and let the entire pot simmer on low heat 10-15 minutes.
